description:
&lt;p&gt;Role:&lt;strong&gt;Nursing Associate Project Team Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 4&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours:1.0 WTE = 37.5hrs- 9 month secondment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Project management Team, Level 7, Derriford, University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trainee Nursing Associate (TNA) Project team have an opportunity to recruit an administrator to support the work they are undertaking around the development and recruitment of the TNA. This project is currently funded by Healthcare Education England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great development opportunity for an experienced administrator and a really exciting time to be part of this team, who are reviewing and evaluating the TNA delivery, both at UHP and across Devon. The objective of the project is to deliver the TNA on mass and at pace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team we are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to support the Nursing Associate project team, providing a comprehensive and high level administration service to enable the project agenda to be delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide an effective, comprehensive and confidential range of administrative / secretarial tasks to ensure the smooth running of the project function and responsibilities. With the ability to establish working relationships at all levels, internal and external to the Trust. An excellent level of IT skills is essential to ensure and extend the internal and external communications for the project as well as excellent record keeping and collation of data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 13 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 23 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more or discuss this opportunity further please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nicola Brockie&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Programme Lead – Telephone 01752 436002&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: nicola.brockie@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
